    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A principal class of soap that is created using fatty acids that are longer and tend to dissolve more slowly in water than soft soaps; for example, olive oil and caustic soda lye would be used to create a hard soap.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
